amed salmon with broccoli pesto<\/em> or <em>Lemon chicken and crispy potatoes<\/em>.","Use up leftover aioli throughout the week on sandwiches, rolls, salads and wraps. Homemade aioli complements many different flavours.","If your aioli has not thickened after step 4, mix for a further <b>2 min\/speed 4<b> <b>or until a mayonnaise consistency is achieved.","<b>Garlic aioli<b>: omit the lemon zest and capers. Add 1- 2 extra garlic cloves to taste in step 1 and proceed as per recipe.","<b>Lemon aioli<b>: omit the capers. Add an extra 1 - 2 pieces of lemon zest (5 x 2 cm) to taste in step 1 and proceed as per recipe.","<b>Citrus aioli<b>: omit the capers and use a combination of orange, lemon and lime zest pieces (5 x 2 cm) in stp 1 to create your flavour of choice. Proceed as per recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","15m","1 total recipe"]}